annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein S6; May play an important role in controlling cell growth and proliferation through the selective translation of particular classes of mRNA
annotationB: Rat1 5'-3' exoribonuclease (Rat1) is a member of the 5'-3' exonuclease family. Rat1 is required for mRNA processing and mutations cause phenotypes in various cell types, including the nervous system
